    -- This involves calculating the derivative of the composition of f with the interpolator.
    -- The interpolator is a linear function, so its derivative is constant.
    -- The derivative of the composition is then the derivative of f evaluated at the interpolator multiplied by the derivative of the interpolator.
    -- Since the interpolator is linear, its derivative is the difference between y and x.
    -- The derivative of f is given by its partial derivatives, so we need to sum over the partial derivatives multiplied by the differences.
    simp [interpolated, interpolator, interpolated_deriv]
